---
// Honest-limits teaser. Links to the dedicated /limits page.
// Strategic intent: pre-empt the Habr "it says all-fixed while real
// contradictions slip through" objection by naming the limit on our own
// terms, before the comment thread does. Confidence comes from candor.
---

<section class="limits-teaser section section--flush-top" aria-labelledby="limits-teaser-title">
  <div class="section-inner section-inner--prose">
    <h2 id="limits-teaser-title" class="limits-teaser__title">
      Here's what it won't catch.
    </h2>
    <p class="limits-teaser__body">
      A linter that claims it catches everything is lying. SpecScore is a
      layered system — a deterministic linter, an AI reviewer, and your own
      judgment — and each layer has a real edge. We wrote them all down: what
      lint catches, what the AI catches, and what's still on you because no tool
      can do it yet.
    </p>
    <p class="limits-teaser__cta">
      <a class="xref" href="/validators/#limits">What the linter won't catch →</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .limits-teaser { background: var(--cream); }
  .limits-teaser__title {
    font-size: var(--fs-h2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .limits-teaser__body {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
</style>
